title: Microsoft Azure Firewall: SNAT Consumption
agents: azure_v2
catalog: cloud/azure
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the SNAT (Source Network Address Translation) port
 utilization of Microsoft Azure Firewalls. It reports the percentage of
 outbound SNAT ports currently in use.

 You can configure the warning and critical levels using the rule
 "Azure Firewall SNAT".

 In order to use this check, you need to configure the Azure special agent.

discovery:
 One service is created for each Azure Firewall.
